A password masking jQuery plugin
By Damian Nicholson

http://damiannicholson.com
http://twitter.com/damian

Info
-------------------------------------
Allows a user to see their password in plaintext if they're unsure
that they've typed it correctly. This is toggled through the use
of a checkbox.

Usage
-------------------------------------
$('input[type="password"]').passwordMask();

Options
-------------------------------------
Hidden - makes the default behaviour to show the passwords in plaintext
$('input[type="password"]').passwordMask({ hidden: false });

Checkbox label - defaults to 'Show password'
$('input[type="password"]').passwordMask({ checkboxlabel: 'Show password in plaintext' });
